p: For the matter of the complaint of Martin Raneon M'ad for a writ of Habeas Corpus and now come the Plaintiffs by their Attorneys and object to the bill filed in court this 16th day of December 1876, to the item by L. V. Wyckoff deputy United States Marshall and to the following specific times to the item of three dollars per day for attendance before D. S. Smith To the items for serving process in which to filed. And to attend. Andrews Ally for Plantiff
